caption: After waiting on hold for 20 minutes. I placed my order. I asked for pan crust and was told they only do pan in the medium size. I said ok that’s fine we will do medium size so we can get the pan crust. They said it would be 45-55 minutes. When they called to say they were 5 minutes away they asked if we could meet them at the lobby because last time he got stuck in the elevator. I was giving kids baths so sent my husband. We received 2 hand tossed crust pizzas- which my kids are just picky and won’t eat.  That’s why I ordered the pan crust. So pbj for 3 disappointed kids on vacay. And on the phone for another ten minutes to talk to person at dominoes only to be told she has to get the manager and then I get cut off. Maybe a mistake? Call back and another ten minutes on hold to talk to another person (who took my original order). Told he has to get a manager. Okay. Manager tells me he will not refund my money because I received product. Said he would make new pizzas and send them out. He must not understand how kids work because when I said my kids were going to bed we can’t wait another hour for remade pizzas, he scoffed that it was only 8:30. He told me he cannot give a refund because that would be punishing a business for making a mistake. And when I said he was punishing me and making me pay for something I didn’t order, he said he thought I just didn’t want to get a solution because he was willing to replace it. I said I was more than happy to give him his pizza back but I had to get my kids to sleep.  He offered credit if he could pick up the pizza I asked what time could he come tomorrow because it was too late tonight and he started hemming and hawing. Mediocre already cold pizza is not worth this hassle. This franchise is ridiculous- I should have just paid resort prices and gotten pizza from the on-site venue.
